<br>
The majority of the people in the United States are Christian and as such they take off on Christmas Day because it is a sacred holiday to them.<br>
<br>
In deference to the fact that a majority of the work force wishes to exercise it's right to freedom of religion, federal employees are given Christmas Day off.<br>
<br>
Federal employees also get Float Holidays which they can take for such days as Yom Kippur or Samhain.<br>
<br>
If the majority of your work force is going to take the day off, you might as well plan for it, yes?  <br>
<br>
By the way, although my state government employer gives us off for Christmas, I and several others often work.  <br>
<br>
This is not favouring any one religion over another.<br>
<br>
To have children led in a recitation of a pledge with pays homage to a monotheistic diety *is* respecting the monotheistic Judeo-Christian faith.<br>
<br>
I can't make it any clearer than that &lt;shrug&gt; <p><TABLE align=left>
