<br>
The two words in the pledge are simply a religious assertion, with no secular aspects.<br>
<br>
It's possible for the government to say &quot;Dec. 25 is a holiday, per the public's desire for that, with many celebrating Christmas&quot;, since so many do. That leaves room for others to simply get the day off and not celebreate religiously.<br>
<br>
If the pledge said &quot;One Nation, under God for those who believe that&quot;, it would both be more similar, and pointless.<br>
<br>
At the moment, the pledge has the teach telling her children a religious assertion, unlike the holiday.<br>
<br>
The holiday is a somewha gray area, and we do our best to balance; it's hard to see a real problem with the holiday. <p>Arch Mage 60, Master of the epic elemental magics, collector of robes<BR><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~craig234/eq/sig/jaharad.gif" border="0">
