It's not religious OR cultural, it has both aspects.<br>
<br>
The thing you miss is not that the teach says God, it's that the teacher proclaims in the pledge the religious statement that the nation is under a deity. That is the issue - the teach can talk about God as part of education, but it's another matter to have a pledge asserting the religious opinion.<br>
